
[1]christs-thorn

   CHRISTS-THORN, n. The Rhamnus paliurus, a deciduous shrub, a native of
   Palestine and the South of Europe. It has two thorns at each joint, and
   is supposed to have been the sort of which the crown of thorns for our
   Savior was made.
